Material Information Summary – Gateway Mining Limited (ASX: GML)

Type: Extraordinary General Meeting (EGM) – Capital Structure & Related Party Transactions

  1. Key Resolutions
  2. Resolution 1: Approval to issue 1.5 billion Convertible Preference Shares (CPS) to Strickland Metals Ltd as consideration for acquiring the Yandal Gold Project (requires Listing Rule 7.1 approval).

  12. EGM: 18 August 2025.
  13. CPS Issuance: 19 August 2025.
  14. In-Specie Distribution: 25 August 2025 (to Strickland shareholders).

  15. Automatic Conversion to Ordinary Shares: 26 August 2025.

  16. Voting Exclusions

  17. Votes from Strickland, Peter Langworthy, Trent Franklin, and their associates will be disregarded for relevant resolutions.

Conclusion: Approval would significantly dilute existing shareholders but provide GML with the Yandal Gold Project. Related party participation requires separate shareholder consent.

Material Information Summary (Sun Silver Limited – ASX Announcement 18 July 2025)

Key Highlights:

  • Re-assay Results:
  • Initial re-assay of 5 historical drill holes (MR059, MR063, MR065, MR069, MR098) shows ~25% higher silver grades on average using four-acid digest method.
  • Grade uplifts by range:
    • >100g/t Ag: +26% (e.g., 106.8g/t → 137g/t median)
    • 10–100g/t Ag: +22% (e.g., 19.3g/t → 24.8g/t median)

  • Potential resource upgrade: Uplifts may support a revised Maverick Springs JORC Resource (current: 296.5Moz Ag, 2.2Moz Au).

  • Ongoing Program:

  • Re-assaying ~195 additional historic holes (30 submitted, 25 pending results).
  • Focus on antimony (Sb) and multi-element analysis, with potential silver grade reassessment.

Implications:

  • Valuation Impact: Consistent grade uplifts suggest historical silver grades may have been understated, potentially enhancing project economics.
  • Next Steps: Further assays, twin drilling, and metallurgical reviews planned.
